As of June 30, 2024, Lotus Technology had 207 stores in its global distribution network. Major vehicle models currently in Lotus Technology's global sales and distribution network include Eletre, Emeya, and future lifestyle models, as well as certain sports car models that were or will be developed and manufactured by Lotus UK, such as Evija (BEV sports car) and Emira (ICE sports car). Key Components of Results of Operations Lotus Technology generates revenues primarily through sales of goods and services. Sales of goods. Lotus Technology generates revenues by providing the following products: ● Battery Electric Vehicle (BEV) lifestyle models developed by Lotus Technology;  
● Lotus-brand sports cars developed by Lotus UK;  
● auto parts; and  
● peripheral products.

